a 20-minute board game for two players
EQUIPMENT:
This game may be played on a 5x5 board,
or a 7x7 board. You’ll need 2 sets of 13
or 25 markers, depending on which you play.
HOW TO PLAY:
There are two phases of play: adding and
subtracting.
ADDING:
Players take turns placing two markers into
squares on the board. Once placed, markers
do not move.
The center square may not be used in this
phase.
SUBTRACTING:
Players take turns moving one marker up,
down, left, or right, trying to capture their
opponent’s markers. If a move results in a
capture, the same player moves again. If a
player has no moves, they may take one of their
opponent’s markers.
CAPTURE:
Markers are captured when they are adjacent
to one enemy piece, and an enemy marker is
moved into an empty square on the opposite
side. More than one marker can be captured
in a single move.
STRATEGY:
The edge points are more secure, and therefore more valuable.
